---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import circleLogo from "../assets/logos/vpsb-circle-logo.png";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why this site has no feed — Vibin' Psybin and the Sunlight Band"
  description="Short-form content makes you dumber. This site is the alternative. New music, videos, shows, and merch — when there's something worth telling you. No feed, no algorithm, no daily anything."
>
  <article class="manifesto">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <Image
        src={circleLogo}
        alt=""
        widths={[120, 200]}
        sizes="100px"
        class="mark"
      />
      <p class="eyebrow">The Why</p>
      <h1>Why this site has no feed</h1>

      <div class="body">
        <p>
          Short-form content makes you dumber. It makes you unhappy. There&rsquo;s research on it
          now &mdash; but you didn&rsquo;t need a study to feel it.
        </p>

        <p>
          I make music. I make videos for the music. I make cover art and the occasional
          hand-stamped CD. That&rsquo;s the work. That&rsquo;s all I want to make.
        </p>

        <p>
          So I&rsquo;m not going to spend my life chasing a 30-second hook for an algorithm that
          will, <em>maybe</em>, show my song to 3% of the people who already chose to follow me.
          And then take a cut of every dollar that comes back, while making
          billionaires richer in the process. Fuck that.
        </p>

        <p class="callout">
          <strong>This site is the alternative.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          If you sign up to the email list, you&rsquo;ll get an email when there&rsquo;s something
          worth telling you. New music. New video. A show in your town. New merch.
        </p>

        <p>
          Probably more often than you&rsquo;d think &mdash; I make a lot of music. But never
          daily, never noisy, never just to be in your inbox.
        </p>

        <p>
          No feed to scroll. No &ldquo;engagement&rdquo; hooks. No notifications begging for your
          attention. Just dank art for the people who give a shit.
        </p>

        <p class="cta-line">
          If that&rsquo;s you &mdash; welcome.
          <br/>
          <a class="btn btn-solid" href="/subscribe">Sign me up &rarr;</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          If not, no hard feelings. Streaming services know where to find me too.
        </p>

        <p class="signoff">
          &mdash; Joe
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .manifesto {
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem 2rem;
    }
    .mark {
      width: 80px;
      height: auto;
      filter: invert(1) brightness(0.95);
      opacity: 0.9;
      margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
      display: block;
    }
    .eyebrow {
      text-align: center;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5.5vw, 3.75rem);
      line-height: 1.1;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
      max-width: 18ch;
    }

    .body {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--fg);
    }
    .body p {
      margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    }
    .body em {
      color: var(--accent);
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .callout {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-2);
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
      margin: 2rem 0 !important;
    }
    .callout strong {
      color: var(--fg);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .cta-line {
      text-align: center;
      margin: 2.5rem 0 !important;
    }
    .cta-line .btn {
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .signoff {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      margin-top: 2.5rem !important;
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
